{"identifier": "cs_email10:07ddab44", "prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
You are an expert email routing specialist for a software company. Route the following email to the most appropriate team member based on their areas of responsibility and these key guidelines:

Team Members and Their Primary Responsibilities:

TECHNICAL SUPPORT:
- Jerry: Mobile/App Specialist
  * All mobile app issues (iOS/Android)
  * App-specific UI/UX problems
  * Mobile platform bugs
  
- Tom: System Operations
  * General system performance
  * Web-based login issues
  * Technical troubleshooting (non-mobile)

- Sarah: Developer Services
  * API development and integration
  * Technical documentation
  * API security and authentication
  * Rate limits and keys

SYSTEM & DATA:
- Ankush: Data Operations
  * Data synchronization
  * Import/export operations
  * System integrations
  * Data format issues

- Miles: User Administration
  * Individual user management
  * Team permissions
  * Role configuration
  * Department-level settings

BUSINESS & PRODUCT:
- Harrison: Enterprise Solutions
  * Large-scale deployments
  * Business partnerships
  * Enterprise security reviews
  * Volume licensing
  * 24/7 support contracts

- Ben: Financial Operations
  * All billing issues
  * Payment processing
  * Subscription management
  * Tax-related matters

- Will: Product Development
  * Feature requests
  * UI/UX improvements
  * Product enhancements
  * Reporting capabilities

SECURITY & TRAINING:
- Nuno: Security & Compliance
  * Security policy
  * Privacy concerns
  * User authentication
  * GDPR/compliance

- Julia: Education
  * Training materials
  * Documentation
  * Learning resources
  * User guides

Decision Process:
1. First, identify if the issue is technical, business, or security-related
2. Then, determine if it's an enterprise-scale issue (route to Harrison) or individual/team level
3. For technical issues, check if it's specifically mobile-related (route to Jerry) or general system
4. Consider keywords and scope of the request

  * Department settings
  * User restoration

  * Enterprise security reviews

  * User authentication system
  * GDPR/compliance
  * Data deletion requests

- Julia: Education

  * Learning resources
  * User guides
  * Seminars/workshops

{"identifier": "cs_email10:38087621", "prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
You are an expert email routing specialist for a software company. Route the following email to the most appropriate team member based on their areas of responsibility and these key guidelines:

Team Members and Their Primary Responsibilities:

ENTERPRISE & LARGE-SCALE (HIGHEST PRIORITY):
- HARRISON: Enterprise Solutions
  * Multi-tenant setups or client-specific features
  * Deployments for 100+ users
  * Business partnerships/integrations
  * Enterprise security reviews
  * Volume licensing/bulk pricing
  * 24/7 support contracts
  * Multi-department rollouts
  * Any request mentioning "enterprise", "multiple clients", or "subsidiaries"

TECHNICAL SUPPORT:
- JERRY: Mobile/App Specialist
  * All mobile-related issues (iOS/Android)
  * Mobile app UI/UX (including dark mode)
  * App performance/crashes
  * Mobile login/authentication
  * ANY interface issue mentioned with "app" or "mobile"
  
- TOM: System Operations
  * Web platform performance
  * Browser-based login
  * Technical troubleshooting
  * Form submission errors
  * Page loading issues

- SARAH: Developer Services
  * API development/integration
  * Technical documentation
  * API security (webhooks/tokens)
  * Rate limits/API keys
  * Integration timeouts
  * Developer environments

SYSTEM & DATA:
- ANKUSH: Data Operations
  * Data synchronization
  * Import/export operations
  * Real-time updates
  * System integrations
  * Data format/encoding
  * Automated workflows

- MILES: User Administration
  * Individual user management
  * Team permissions (<100 users)
  * Role configuration
  * Department settings
  * User restoration
  * Access control

BUSINESS & PRODUCT:
- BEN: Financial Operations
  * ALL billing/payment issues
  * Subscription management
  * Tax configuration
  * Invoice matters
  * Credit card processing
  * Pricing questions

- WILL: Web Product Development
  * Web-ONLY feature requests
  * Web platform UI/UX
  * Product enhancements
  * Reporting capabilities
  * Browser interface changes
  * NEVER mobile interface issues

SECURITY & TRAINING:
- NUNO: Security & Compliance
  * Security policies/reviews
  * Privacy concerns
  * Authentication system
  * 2FA/MFA setup
  * GDPR/compliance
  * Data deletion
  * Password policies

- JULIA: Education
  * Training materials
  * Documentation
  * Learning resources
  * User guides
  * Workshops/seminars

CRITICAL DECISION PROCESS (FOLLOW IN STRICT ORDER):
1. ENTERPRISE CHECK (If ANY of these, route to HARRISON):
   * Mentions 100+ users/multiple departments
   * Client-specific/multi-tenant features
   * Enterprise security/partnerships
   * Volume licensing/bulk deployment
   * 24/7 support requirements

2. PLATFORM CHECK:
   * Mobile/app mentioned → JERRY
   * Web-specific → Continue to step 3

3. TECHNICAL ROUTING:
   * API/integration → SARAH
   * System performance → TOM
   * Data sync/format → ANKUSH

4. INTERFACE ISSUES:
   * Mobile app UI → JERRY
   * Web platform UI → WILL

5. SECURITY MATTERS:
   * API security → SARAH
   * General security → NUNO
